{
  "texts": [
    "The first phase encourages one to observe and pay close attention to fine details to develop relevant information.",
    "Next, in the collecting phase, findings from the previous phase specifically relevant information are gathered systematically.",
    "This includes a more comprehensive analysis of data from a variety range of sources and perspectives to facilitate the next phase.",
    "Finally, information is interpreted intelligently and critically considering different viewpoints.",
    "This approach is different from other qualitative data analysis approaches since this approach can be adopted in various contexts like research, problem-solving, and decision-making; and integrating noticing-collecting-thinking a topic or subject can be well understood before concluding."
  ]
}